'''Line 18 - Bronze''' is a future project of the [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro]]. It will link [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo (city)|S<U+00E3>o Paulo]] to the southeast portion of the [[Greater S<U+00E3>o Paulo]], ending in [[S<U+00E3>o Bernardo do Campo]]. The line is expected to be the first one in the local [[rapid transit]] system to go beyond the city limits. <ref name="DGABC1" /> <ref name="OESP20120203"> {{cite news | newspaper = O Estado de S. Paulo | date = February 3, 2012 | accessdate = March 15, 2014 | language = Portuguese | url = http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20120203-43207-spo-36-cid-c8-not/busca/Linha+18+Bronze | title = Governo quer terceirizar o monotrilho do ABC | trans_title = Government wants to outsource ABC monorail | page = C8 | last = Ribeiro | first = Bruno }} </ref>

== Background ==

Preliminary studies for a city passenger rail transportation system in S<U+00E3>o Paulo were sketched as of [[1888]] <ref name="OESP20130125"> {{cite news | newspaper = O Estado de S. Paulo | language = Portuguese | date = January 25, 2013 | accessdate = March 13, 2014 | url = http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20130125-43564-nac-58-cid-h4-not/busca/Alberto+Kuhlmann | title = Em 1888, engenheiro alem<U+00E3>o tentou - sem sucesso - fazer monotrilho no centro | trans_title = In 1888, a German engineer tried - unsuccessfully - to build a monorail downtown | page = H4 }} </ref>, and later some of them included the so-called [[ABC region]]. One of them cited a [[suspension railway]] as an alternative for the city and its neighborhoods in the [[1960s]], inspired on [[Wuppertal Suspension Railway]] and [[SAFEGE]] models, including a suggestion to link ABC to [[Parque Dom Pedro II]] through [[Tamanduate<U+00ED> River]]. <ref name="OESP19660102"> {{cite news | date = January 2, 1966 | newspaper = O Estado de S. Paulo | accessdate = March 13, 2014 | language = Portuguese | url = http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/19660102-27824-nac-0020-999-20-not/busca/ABC+linha+metr%C3%B4 | title = Preconizado o metro a<U+00E9>reo como solu<U+00E7><U+00E3>o para a Capital | trans_title = Predicting elevated metro as a solution for the capital | page = 20 }} </ref>

S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro was established as a company in [[1968]] and started its revenue service in [[1974]]. <ref name="MSP1"> {{cite web | website = S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro website | title = About Us | url = http://www.metro.sp.gov.br/en/metro/about-us/index.aspx | accessdate = March 12, 2014 }} </ref> Its justification was based upon the fast growth of the city of S<U+00E3>o Paulo, and its car fleet as well, with all the problems emerging due to that. The original plan suggested the construction of four lines, all of them enclosed within the city's limits, although predicting transfer stations to the commuter rail system and the buses. The southeasternmost station of the system was predicted to be settled near [[Via Anchieta]] (and bearing such name), a state road linking S<U+00E3>o Paulo to [[Santos, S<U+00E3>o Paulo|Santos]] passing by the ABC region. <ref name="OESP19681121"> {{cite news | date = November 21, 1968 | accessdate = March 12, 2014 | newspaper = O Estado de S. Paulo | language = Portuguese | url = http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/19681121-28718-nac-0090-999-90-not/busca/S%C3%A3o+Paulo+metr%C3%B4 | title = Passageiros, o metro j<U+00E1> vai partir | page = 90 | trans_title = Passengers, the metro will depart | last = de Siqueira | first = Ethevaldo Mello }} </ref>

Although [[commuter rail]] services exist between the ABC region and the city of S<U+00E3>o Paulo since the end of the [[19th century]], through [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo Railway]] and its successors, the fast growing of the area observed in the 2nd half of the [[20th century]] and the unavailability of such services on some cities (notably S<U+00E3>o Bernardo do Campo and [[Diadema]]) demanded further transport options to the region. At first the government didn't see any rationale to establish a metro line in the area, choosing to install a [[trolley bus]] service linking S<U+00E3>o Paulo to S<U+00E3>o Bernardo do Campo through Diadema. <ref name="OESP19841130"> {{cite news | language = Portuguese | url = http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/19841130-33665-nac-0036-999-36-not/busca/Metr%C3%B4+linha+ABC | newspaper = O Estado de S. Paulo | date = November 30, 1984 | accessdate = March 12, 2014 | page = 36 | title = Obras de tr<U+00F3>lebus no ABC come<U+00E7>am este ano | trans_title = Trolley bus works start this year }} </ref> Such initiative leaded to the establishment of [[S<U+00E3>o Mateus<U+2013>Jabaquara metropolitan corridor]], one of the first [[bus rapid transit]] systems in Brazil.

The [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo (state)|S<U+00E3>o Paulo]] secretariat of Metropolitan Transportation started to issue plans for the future transport expansion in 1997, aiming to anticipate and get prepared for the demands of its citizens on this matter. Those reports are known as Integrated Urban Transport Plans (''Plano Integrado de Transporte Urbano'' - PITU). <ref name="STM"> {{cite web | website = Metropolitan Transportation Secretary website | accessdate = March 14, 2014 | date = August 9, 2009 | title = PITU Presentations | url = http://www.stm.sp.gov.br/index.php/pitu2020-english-327 }} </ref> PITU [[2025]] claimed for the need to a metro branch linking ABC to S<U+00E3>o Paulo, more specifically employing either a [[light rail]] or [[guided bus]] technology. <ref name="PITU25"> {{cite web | website = S<U+00E3>o Paulo Secretariat of Metropolitan Transportation | language = Portuguese | title = PITU 2025 | page = 196 | url = http://www.stm.sp.gov.br/images/stories/Pitus/Pitu2025/Pdf/Pitu_2025_08.pdf | accessdate = March 17, 2014 | date = December 2006 }} </ref>

== Project ==

{{BS-map
|title= {{color box|#964b00|Line 18 - Bronze|white}} <ref name="G12"> {{cite web | language = Portuguese | website = g1.com.br | accessdate = March 18, 2014 | date = January 28, 2014 | url = http://g1.globo.com/sao-paulo/noticia/2014/01/governo-publica-nesta-quarta-edital-para-monotrilho-que-liga-capital-abc.html | title = Governo publica nesta quarta edtal para monotrilho que liga capital a ABC | trans_title = Government issues procurement for monorail to link the capital to ABC region | last = Santiago | first = Tatiana }} </ref> <ref name="VIAT"> {{cite web | language = Portuguese | website = viatrolebus.com.br | accessdate = March 19, 2014 | url = http://viatrolebus.com.br/2014/01/confira-detalhes-da-linha-18-bronze-que-teve-edital-de-obras-lancado-nesta-quarta-29/ | title = Confira detalhes da Linha 18 - Bronze, que teve edital de obras lan<U+00E7>ado nesta quarta (29) | date = January 29, 2014 | trans_title = Check out details from line 18 - Bronze, whose procurement has been issued on this Wednesday 29 | last = Lobo | first = Renato }} </ref>
