The original project predicted a 18 stops' line linking the current [[Tamanduate<U+00ED> (S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro)|Tamanduate<U+00ED> station]] (already served by S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro and [[CPTM]] [[commuter rail]] service as well) to Alvarengas station, a future terminal station to be located near the city road bearing the same name. <ref name="EIARIMA"> {{cite web | website = S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro website | language = Portuguese | accessdate = March 17, 2014 | url = http://www.metro.sp.gov.br/metro/licenciamento-ambiental/pdf/linha_18_bronze/eia/volume-i/Arquivo-01.pdf | title = Estudo de Impacto Ambiental - Linha 18 | trans_title = Environmental impact assessment - Line 18 | page = 1 | date = May 15, 2012 }} </ref> However parts of such path overlaps the current S<U+00E3>o Mateus<U+2013>Jabaquara metropolitan corridor, which would demand the extinction of such service between S<U+00E3>o Bernardo and Ferraz<U+00F3>polis. As this corridor is operated through a [[Concession (contract)|concession]], it would imply breaking that [[contract]] thus exposing the state government to a [[termination fee]]. Such risk endangered the whole project <ref name="DGABC20130623"> {{cite web | website = Di<U+00E1>rio do Grande ABC website | date = June 23, 2013 | accessdate = March 17, 2014 | language = Portuguese | url = http://www.dgabc.com.br/Noticia/463876/linha-18-bronze-ate-o-alvarenga-tem-chance-de-ficar-so-no-papel?referencia=buscas-lista | title = Linha 18 - Bronze at<U+00E9> o Alvarenga tem chance de ficar s<U+00F3> no papel | trans_title = Line 18 - Bronze to Alvarenga in risk to remain as a project | last = Rocha | first = Rafael }} </ref> and the solution sought was to truncate the proposed line to end at S<U+00E3>o Bernardo station and eventually at Djalma Dutra station.

The [[government procurement]] for the establishment of the line has been established in [[2014]] and states it will be constructed as a [[public<U+2013>private partnership]]. The system is expected to be concluded in [[2018]]. <ref name="DGABC20140129"> {{cite web | website = Di<U+00E1>rio do Grande ABC website | language = portuguese | date = January 29, 2014 | accessdate = March 17, 2014 | last = Rocha | first = Raphael | title = Alckmin planeja divulgar vencedor da Linha 18 no 1<U+00BA> semestre | trans_title = Alckmin plans to announce line 18 winner up to the 1st half-year | url = http://www.dgabc.com.br/Noticia/507410/alckmin-planeja-divulgar-vencedor-da-linha-18-no-1-semestre?referencia=buscas-lista }} </ref>

Stations ''Rudge Ramos'' and ''Mau<U+00E1>'' are shown as ''Pra<U+00E7>a Regina Matiello'' and ''Instituto Mau<U+00E1>'', respectively, in some local news sources <ref name="VIAT" /> <ref name="Terra"> {{cite web | website = terra.com.br | accessdate = March 19, 2014 | url = http://www.terra.com.br/noticias/infograficos/metro-novas-estacoes/ | title = A evolu<U+00E7><U+00E3>o das obras do metro e CPTM | trans_title = Evolution of Metro and CPTM works | language = Portuguese }} </ref>, although the most recent metro company documents still don't mention them bearing such names. <ref name="MSPD"> {{cite web | website = S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro website | language = Portuguese | url = http://www.metro.sp.gov.br/obras/desapropriacoes/linha-18-bronze.aspx | title = Desapropria<U+00E7><U+00F5>es - Linha 18 Bronze | trans_title = Resumptions - Line 18 Bronze | accessdate = March 19, 2014 }} </ref>

==Controversy==

The monorail alternative for line 18 was contested, as it is not employed on current metro branches but appointed as the most suitable construction for this project, as well as for lines [[Line 15 (S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro)|15]] (formerly line [[Line 2 (S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro)|2]] expansion) and [[Line 17 (S<U+00E3>o Paulo Metro)|17]]. Positive arguments are the cheaper, faster construction and decreasing the need for [[Eminent domain|resumption]]; listed setbacks are [[visual pollution]], difficulty to be evacuated in case of emergency, its relative small capacity and incapability to be upgraded. <ref name="OESP20120319"> {{cite news | newspaper = O Estado de S. Paulo | date = March 19, 2012 | accessdate = March 14, 2014 | language = Portuguese | url = http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20120319-43252-spo-32-cid-c6-not/busca/LINHA+18 | title = O monotrilho <U+00E9> uma boa ou m<U+00E1> op<U+00E7><U+00E3>o para SP? | trans_title = Is monorail a good or bad option for S<U+00E3>o Paulo? | last = Brancatelli | first = Rodrigo | last2 = Cavaleiro | first2 = Carolina | last3 = M<U+00FC>ller | first3 = Marcos | page = C6 }} </ref>

In downtown S<U+00E3>o Bernardo do Campo, some real estate owners tried to settle a [[civil action]] to change the proposed [[Right-of-way (transportation)|right-of-way]], as it may adversely affect [[high-end]] [[apartment building]]s recently erected there, through aesthetic concerns and planned resumptions. <ref name="G1"> {{cite web | website = g1.com.br | url = http://g1.globo.com/sao-paulo/noticia/2013/07/moradores-querem-acao-judicial-contra-tracado-de-monotrilho-no-abc.html | accessdate = March 17, 2014 | date = July 8, 2013 | last = Santiago | first = Tatiana | language = Portuguese | trans_title = Homeowners want civil action against ABC monorail path | title = Moradores querem a<U+00E7><U+00E3>o judicial contra tra<U+00E7>ado de monotrilho no ABC }} </ref>

